wiki.summary: bbno$ and Rich Brian team up for the first time on “edamame”, a song produced by Diamond Pistols and the second single off of bbno$’s sixth album "eat ya veggies". The song sees Alex and Brian rapping about finally getting paid for making hit songs and the popularity of their names and music. The song snippets were posted on both Alex’s and Brian’s Instagram stories a week before the release. Besides the officially released version, there is an unreleased meme version of the song with bbno$ rapping over the Mii Channel melody. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: bbno$ and Rich Brian team up for the first time on “edamame”, a song produced by Diamond Pistols and the second single off of bbno$’s sixth album "eat ya veggies". The song sees Alex and Brian rapping about finally getting paid for making hit songs and the popularity of their names and music. The song snippets were posted on both Alex’s and Brian’s Instagram stories a week before the release. Besides the officially released version, there is an unreleased meme version of the song with bbno$ rapping over the Mii Channel melody. Diamond Pistols claims that this is the best song he has ever produced: "when i say this is the best song i’ve ever produced i fully mean it" bbno$ uploaded a special lyric video for this song with subtitles in Indonesian on his YouTube channel.
